# Technical Report (Condensed)

**Purpose:** Document technical work that doesn't fit paper format.

**Links to:** experiment-tracking, research-design, thesis-writing, paper-writing

---

## Report Types

### 1. Experiment Report
- Objective, Setup (hardware/software/dataset/hyperparameters), Method, Results (main + ablation + stats), Analysis, Conclusions, Reproducibility

### 2. System Design Document
- Overview, Requirements (functional + non-functional), Architecture (high-level + components + data flow), API Design, Database, Deployment, Testing, Monitoring, Security

### 3. Code Documentation
- Overview, Installation, Quick Start, API Reference (classes, methods, params, returns, exceptions), Configuration, Changelog

### 4. Research Memo
- Context, Key Observations, Analysis, Implications, Action Items

## Experiment Report Template

```markdown
# Experiment Report: [Name]

## Objective
[Question this experiment answers]

## Setup
- Hardware: GPU type × count, RAM
- Software: Python, PyTorch, CUDA versions
- Dataset: name, size, splits, preprocessing
- Hyperparameters: search ranges, final values

## Results
| Method | Accuracy | F1 | Latency |
|--------|----------|-----|---------|
| Baseline | 85.2±0.3 | 84.1±0.4 | 12ms |
| Ours | 87.1±0.2 | 86.3±0.3 | 15ms |

## Statistical Analysis
- Test: paired t-test, p-value: 0.002
- Seeds: 5 (42, 123, 456, 789, 1024)

## Reproducibility
- Code: [URL]
- Data: [URL]
```

## Quality Checklist

- [ ] Clear objective, sufficient detail for reproduction
- [ ] Results with mean ± std, statistical tests
- [ ] Consistent notation, figures/tables with captions
- [ ] Version number, date, code snippets tested
